---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LegalDoc from '~/components/LegalDoc.astro';
import { contactInfo } from '~/i18n/ui';

const locale = 'en' as const;
const email = contactInfo.email;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Yezuri"
  description="Our privacy policy explaining how Yezuri collects, uses and protects your personal data."
  locale={locale}
  canonicalPath="/en/privacy-policy"
  alternatePath="/gizlilik-politikasi"
>
  <LegalDoc eyebrow="Legal" title="Privacy Policy" updatedLabel="Last updated" updated="May 23, 2026">
    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains how Yezuri (“we”, “Yezuri”) processes the personal data we
      collect through <a href="https://yezuri.com">yezuri.com</a> and our related pages. By using
      our site, you accept the practices described here.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
    <p>We may collect the following data from you or your usage:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contact details:</strong> your name, business name, phone/WhatsApp number and email address that you provide via forms or contact channels.</li>
      <li><strong>Communication content:</strong> the content of the messages and requests you send us.</li>
      <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> technical data collected automatically, such as IP address, browser type and pages visited.</li>
      <li><strong>Cookie data:</strong> as described in the “Cookies” section below.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use Data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To respond to your requests and questions and to contact you,</li>
      <li>To provide and operate our services,</li>
      <li>To improve our site and the quality of our services,</li>
      <li>To send promotional and marketing communications where you have given consent,</li>
      <li>To fulfil our legal obligations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      Our site may use cookies and similar technologies for essential functionality (such as theme
      preference) and, optionally, visit analytics. You can control or delete cookies from your
      browser settings; doing so may affect how some parts of the site work.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Sharing of Data</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal data. Your data may only be shared, to the extent necessary, in the following cases:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>With service providers we work with (e.g. hosting, email, CRM, messaging/WhatsApp services),</li>
      <li>Where required by a legal obligation or a request from a competent authority,</li>
      <li>In other cases where you have given explicit consent.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
      We retain your personal data only for as long as the processing purpose requires and for the
      periods stipulated by applicable legislation. At the end of that period your data is deleted,
      destroyed or anonymised.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Your Rights (KVKK / GDPR)</h2>
    <p>
      Under Turkey’s Personal Data Protection Law No. 6698 (KVKK), the GDPR and related legislation,
      you have rights including learning whether your data is processed, requesting information,
      requesting correction or deletion, objecting to processing, and data portability. You can send
      your requests to the contact address below.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Security</h2>
    <p>
      We take reasonable technical and administrative measures to protect your data against
      unauthorised access, loss and misuse. However, please note that no transmission over the
      internet is 100% secure.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Third-Party Links</h2>
    <p>
      Our site may contain links to third-party sites that are not under our control. We are not
      responsible for the privacy practices of those sites.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time. The current version is always published on this
      page; for significant changes we revise the “last updated” date above.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For privacy-related questions and requests, you can reach us at
      <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>.
    </p>
  </LegalDoc>
</BaseLayout>
